On Sunday, March 06, 2005, at 10:33AM, Tom Shinn <turtlebus(-at-)msn.com> wrote:

>I am using a VDO oil pressure sender with a VDO extension hose. I have read
>conflicting things about the thread on the end of the hose that threads into
>the case so I used an adapter that has the metric npt threads in the case and
>threaded the hose into that. The hose sealed into the adapter but the adapter
>didn't seal into the case. pulled the adapter and fount that the threads are
>not tapered on the adapter and are not long enough to get tight in the case.

Anytime the threads no non tapered you will need to use a crush washer.

